text: The Kackeschbaach (part of it is also known as the Kettebaach) is a tributary of the Syre in the communes of Sandweiler and Contern in Luxembourg. It flows from the South of Sandweiler out east before heading further south, roughly following Route de Remich through Eitermillen and it ends in Oetrange. Category:Rivers of Luxembourg
title: Kackeschbaach
